LEARNING OBJECTIVE OF THIS COURSE:


This course  introduced me to Amazon Web Services (AWS) serverless architecture. Through demonstrations and hands-on exercises I learnT skills in building and deploying serverless solutions. 

Using real-world examples of a serverless website and chat bot, I build upon MY existing knowledge of the AWS cloud to take advantage of the benefits of modern architectures for greater agility, innovation, and lower total cost of ownership across a range of AWS services, including AWS Lambda, Amazon API Gateway, Amazon DynamoDB, and Amazon Lex.

In this course, I had the option to complete hands-on exercises. strongly suggested to take advantage of the AWS Free Tier which I did to follow the lab exercises provided by throughout the course.Class forums  also helped me to ask questions and interact with AWS training instructors. After completing this course, I gained the knowledge and skills to build serverless solutions on AWS. 


WHAT I LEARNT:

1.Introduce AWS serverless framework and architecture in the context of a real business problem
2.Provide the foundational knowledge to become more proficient in choosing and creating serverless solutions using AWS
3.Provide demonstrations of AWS Lambda, Amazon API Gateway, Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon Lex, and other services needed to deploy serverless solutions.

SKILLS DEVELOPED:

1.AWS Lambda
2.Amazon Lex
3.Amazon API Gateway
3.serverless architecture
4.Amazon Dynamodb
